Bullet Charts
Bullet charts are perfect for comparing metrics against quantitative benchmarks and references, like current revenue with target revenue.

Create a Bullet Chart
Measure current revenue against target revenue and compare it with last quarter's revenue with a bullet chart.
You can measure current revenue by finding the sum of the amount field.
The background bar represents target revenue, divided into three sections that represent qualitative performance: red for bad, yellow for good, and green for great.
The black bar shows the current revenue. The blue reference line marks last quarter's revenue.

In the lens, click  and then select the Bullet chart type.
Add the measure that you want to analyze, like sum of amount.
To customize the bullet chart, click  and set the chart properties in the Formatting panel.

Set target revenue by expanding Range Values and setting Max to your target revenue.
Make the bar and bullet bigger by expanding Bullet and setting Range weight to 200 and Bar weight to 40.
Add last quarter's revenue by clicking + Reference Line, setting value to last quarter's revenue, and setting Label to Last Quarter.
Create band colors on the background bar by setting bins in Conditional Formatting.
The bullet chart now makes it easy to see current revenue against target revenue.
title: Understanding Bullet Charts in CRM Analytics
